<br><br><div class="gmail_quote">2008/5/30 Jeff Squyres &lt;<a href="mailto:jsquyres@cisco.com">jsquyres@cisco.com</a>&gt;:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="border-left: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 0.8ex; padding-left: 1ex;">
I&#39;d also like to re-emphasize something Andreas said earlier: SIGTERM<br>
*usually* means that some external entity is killing your<br>
application. &nbsp;It *could* be coming from within the application itself,<br>
but that&#39;s not too common.<br>
<br>
You might want to look into that to find out where the SIGTERM is<br>
coming from. &nbsp;The Microtar maintainers might have some better ideas.<br>
<div><div></div><div class="Wj3C7c"><br>
